  "text": "Groups of eight 6-week-old female BALB/c mice were mock-infected with PBS, or infected intranasally with [CITATION_1] 7 pfu/mL of M51R or M40 as described previously. [CITATION_2] Body weight measurements were recorded on a daily basis over a two week period while survival was monitored and plotted. At 2 days postinfection, three mice were sacrificed, and viral titers were determined from lung and brain homogenates of sacrificed animals using a standard plaque assay on BHK-21 cells. [CITATION_3] ",
